Arlington Court is an exclusive eight-floor residential development that is being developed along Tanbu Lane in East Legon, a town in the Accra Metropolitan district of the Greater Accra Region, in Ghana. Also Read: Solaris development in Osu, a neighborhood in central Accra, Ghana It features a total of 38 units including 1, 2, and 3-bedroom apartments plus penthouses of apartments with state of the art interior features such as paneled/flush doors, recessed ceiling lighting, fitted wardrobes, air conditioning units, DSTV connection, fiber optic internet connectivity. This is in addition to a washing machine, bathrooms with porcelain tiles, tempered glass balustrades, and water heating systems, and fully fitted kitchens with appliances such as refrigerator, hob & extractor, oven, and microwave.  The gated community also offers a variety of amenities that ensure total wellness and unlimited convenience for residents. These amenities include a rooftop recreational area with an infinity pool, fitness center, lounge and reception, elevator, fire escape staircase, sufficient car parking area. In addition, Arlington Court also has backup water & power supply, property management office, electric security fencing, 24-hour security and concierge services with CCTV monitoring, and fire protection and safety systems. Furthermore, residents have unlimited ease of access to various places of interest within the greater Accra region such as hospitality, retail, business, and sports centers. The project is developed by Whitewall Properties, a Ghanaian-owned real estate Company with over 10 years of industry experience building uniquely designed apartments and townhouses in preferred areas of Accra.